<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
MHD_HTTP_Res_Header declares header and value as char * but MHD_set_connection_value_n_nocheck_ assigns const char *key and const char *value to those members (pos->header = key; pos->value = value;). This discards the const qualifier and shows the members could/should be const char *. The corresponding request struct (MHD_HTTP_Req_Header) already uses const char * for these fields, so the non-const members in MHD_HTTP_Res_Header violate MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13.
</scenario>
